			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently the &amp;quot;-d&amp;quot; debug mode does (at least) two different things:
 * It causes sel_ldr to continue after a validation failure.
 * It enables access to the host system's file namespace,
   i.e. it enables open(), stat() etc.

It would be good to split these into separate options.  That would
make it possible to test programs that need file access, while still
testing that they pass the validator.

For example, glibc's dynamic linker needs to be able to load
libraries, but I want to ensure that it (and the code it loads) passes
the validator.
